children.name: lerp
children.comment:
Performs linear interpolation between values a and b. Returns the value
between a and b proportional to x (when x is between 0 and 1. When x is
outside this range, the return value is a linear extrapolation).

children.name: Vector

children.comment: Adds a [Coordinate] and returns the result as new [Vector].
Multiplies each dimensions by the provided magnitude and returns a new [Vector].

children.name: scale
children.comment: Multiplies each dimensions by the provided magnitude and returns a new [Vector].

children.name: dot
children.comment: Computes the dot product with the given [Vector].

children.name: cross
children.comment: Computes the cross product with the given [Vector].

children.name: getAngle
children.comment:
Computes the angle between this and another [Vector].
Angle zero points in the +X direction, 90 degrees points in the +Y
direction (down) and from there we grow clockwise.

children.name: length
children.comment: Computes the length of this [Vector].

children.name: angle
children.comment:
Returns the angle between the positive x-axis and the [Vector].
Angle zero points in the +X direction, 90 degrees points in the +Y
direction (down) and from there we grow clockwise.
Class reperesenting a 2d vector.

children.name: fitsInside
children.comment:
Returns true if this Size is the same size or smaller than the
[target] size in both dimensions.

children.name: isEmpty
children.comment:
Returns true if the size has zero area, false if both dimensions
    are non-zero numbers.

children.name: scale
children.comment: Multiplies each dimensions by the provided magnitude and returns a new [Size].
Multiplies each dimensions by the provided magnitude and returns a new [Size].

children.name: toString
children.comment:
Returns a nice string representing size.
Returns in the form (50 x 73).

children.name: area
children.comment: Returns the area of the size (width * height).

children.name: aspectRatio
children.comment: Returns the ratio of the size's width to its height.

children.name: perimeter
children.comment: Returns the perimeter of the size (width + height) * 2.

children.name: getDistance
children.comment: Computes the distance to another [Coordinate].
Subtract a [Coordinate] and returns the result as new [Vector].

children.name: add
children.comment:
_I'm not a huge fan of returning a [GlobalId] but at the moment
functions don't have a simple model for identity. [GlobalId] allows
reliable removal of an added handler._

Related dart bug [167](http://code.google.com/p/dart/issues/detail?id=167)

children.name: disposeInternal
children.comment:
Do not call this method directly. Call [dispose] instead.
Subclasses should override this method to implement [Disposable] behavior.

Returns the element at the given [index] in the list or throws
an [IndexOutOfRangeException] if [index] is out of bounds.

children.name: length
children.comment: Returns the number of elements in this collection.

children.name: ReadOnlyCollection.wrap
children.comment: Wraps [source]. Changes to [source] will be reflected.

children.name: ReadOnlyCollection
children.comment:
Copies all of the elements from [source] into a new collection.
Add or removing items in source will not change the contents of the
new collection.
_Note: this is not a **deep** copy._

children.name: containsKey
children.comment: Returns whether this map contains the given [key].

Returns the value for the given [key] or null if [key] is not
in the map. Because null values are supported, one should either
use containsKey to distinguish between an absent key and a null
value, or use the [putIfAbsent] method.

children.name: forEach
children.comment: Applies [f] to each {key, value} pair of the map.

children.name: getKeys
children.comment: Returns a collection containing all the keys in the map.

children.name: length
children.comment: The number of {key, value} pairs in the map.

children.name: isEmpty
children.comment: Returns true if there is no {key, value} pair in the map.

children.name: some
children.comment:
Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the
predicate [f]. Returns false otherwise.

children.name: selectMany
children.comment: Use [expand] instead

children.name: toHashSet
children.comment: Use the [map] method then [toSet] instead.

children.name: toHashMap
children.comment: Use [toMap] instead.

children.name: _ListIterator
children.comment: Iterates over a [List] in growing index order.

children.name: selectMany
children.comment: Use [source.expand] instead.

children.name: toHashMap
children.comment: Use [toMap] instead.

children.name: toHashSet
children.comment: Use `Iterable.map(...).toSet()` instead.

children.name: padLeft
children.comment:
Returns a [String] with a length that is at least [minWidth].
If [text] has a length less than [minWidth], the return value
will be a string with spaces inserted before [text].
